## 2. System Context Diagram (Level 1)

This diagram shows how the system interacts with external users and services.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Student[Student] --> System[Assignment Tracker System]
    System --> Email[Email Service]
```

### Explanation:
- The student is the primary user of the system.
- The system manages assignments and reminders.
- The email service is used to send notifications.

## 3. Container Diagram (Level 2)

This diagram shows the main components of the system.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Student[Student] --> WebApp[Web Application]
    WebApp --> API[Backend API]
    API --> DB[Database]
    API --> Email[Email Service]
```

### Explanation:
- The Web Application provides the user interface.
- The Backend API processes logic and handles requests.
- The Database stores assignment data.
- The Email Service sends reminders.

## 4. Component Diagram (Level 3)

This diagram shows the internal structure of the backend.

```mermaid
graph TD
    API[Backend API] --> Auth[Authentication Module]
    API --> Assign[Assignment Module]
    API --> Reminder[Reminder Module]
```

### Explanation:
- The Authentication Module handles login and registration.
- The Assignment Module manages assignment operations.
- The Reminder Module handles notifications and scheduling.

## 5. End-to-End System Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    Login[Student logs in] --> Add[Add Assignment]
    Add --> Save[Save to Database]
    Save --> Schedule[Schedule Reminder]
    Schedule --> Notify[Send Notification]
```

### Explanation:
This diagram shows how the system works step-by-step:
- The student logs into the system  
-The student adds an assignment  
-The system stores the assignment in the database  
-A reminder is scheduled  
-A notification is sent before the deadline  
